DESCRIPTION:In 1980\, following the September 12 military coup in Türkiye\, thousands are arrested as the nation descends into fear and political chaos. Amid the turmoil\, Abdullah Çatlı\, a young right-wing figure\, is forced to flee abroad. At the same time\, the ASALA terrorist organization launches deadly attacks across Europe\, targeting civilians and Turkish diplomats. Desperate to stop the bloodshed\, the military regime secretly tasks Çatlı and his loyal comrades with fighting ASALA in the heart of Europe—unofficially\, invisibly\, and without acknowledgment.<br/><br/>Their covert war quickly turns deadly. Exposed during a critical operation\, Çatlı becomes both hunter and hunted. Betrayed by hidden political forces in France\, he is imprisoned on false charges\, where the battle follows him behind bars. Outside\, his comrades continue the fight\, while his family is left vulnerable to retaliation. Forced to escape to survive and protect those he loves\, Çatlı pays a devastating personal price. Gravely wounded\, he returns to his safe house—but not everyone survives.<br/><br/>He returns to Türkiye to continue his shadow war… until a mysterious car crash shocks the nation. His struggle seems to end there—or so the world believes.
